4. **Experiment** — one testable hypothesis per plan{% if replan_mode %} (optional in replan mode){% endif %}

5. **Cost** — prefer gas over electric heating, minimize water waste

## Parameter Authority

### Tier 1: Tunable (emit ALL of these at every transition)

**Misting & VPD response:**
| Parameter | Range | Purpose |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| `vpd_hysteresis` | 0.1-0.5 kPa | Dead band around band ceiling. Larger = less cycling. |
| `mister_engage_kpa` | 1.0-1.8 kPa | VPD threshold to start misting. Lower = earlier engagement. |
| `mister_all_kpa` | 1.3-2.2 kPa | VPD threshold for all-zone rotation. Usually engage + 0.3. |
| `mister_pulse_on_s` | 30-90s | Mister burst duration. 60s is the validated sweet spot. |
| `mister_pulse_gap_s` | 10-60s | Evaporation dwell. 15-20s dry days, 45s when humid. |
| `mister_vpd_weight` | 1.0-3.0 | Driest-zone-first weighting. Higher = more zone focus. |
| `mister_water_budget_gal` | 200-500 | Daily water limit. Must never be the bottleneck. |
| `mister_center_penalty` | 0-1.0 | Center zone stress downweight (0.8 = mostly ignore center). |

**Cooling & ventilation:**
| Parameter | Range | Purpose |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| `d_cool_stage_2` | 2-5°F | Gap between COOL_S1 and COOL_S2. Smaller = more aggressive. |
| `lead_rotate_s` | 60-1800s | Fan lead/lag rotation. Shorter on extreme days distributes wear. |
| `min_fan_on_s` | 30-300s | Min fan on-time. Shorter = more responsive cooling. |
| `min_fan_off_s` | 30-300s | Min gap between fan cycles. Prevents relay chatter. |
| `enthalpy_open` | -20 to 5 kJ/kg | Vent opens when outdoor enthalpy is this much better than indoor. More negative = stricter. |
| `enthalpy_close` | -5 to 20 kJ/kg | Vent closes when outdoor enthalpy is this much worse. Wider gap = less vent cycling. |
| `min_vent_on_s` | 10-300s | Min vent open time. Prevents chatter in marginal enthalpy. |
| `min_vent_off_s` | 10-300s | Min vent closed time. |

**Heating & band biases:**
| Parameter | Range | Purpose |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| `bias_heat_f` | -5 to +5°F | Shift heating floor. +2 = pre-heat before cold front. |
| `bias_cool_f` | -5 to +5°F | Shift cooling ceiling. -2 = start cooling earlier before heat wave. |
| `min_heat_on_s` | 60-300s | Min heater on-time per cycle. |
| `min_heat_off_s` | 120-600s | Min gap between heater cycles. |

**Fog:**
| Parameter | Range | Purpose |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| `fog_burst_min` | 1-60 min | Fog minimum runtime per burst. Shorter on dry days (3-5 min). |
| `min_fog_on_s` | 15-300s | Min fog on-time per cycle. Shorter = more responsive fog. |
| `min_fog_off_s` | 15-300s | Min gap between fog cycles. Prevents oversaturation. |

**Zone tuning:**
| Parameter | Range | Purpose |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| `east_adjacency_factor` | 0-1.0 | How much east-zone stress spills misting priority to south/center. 0.3 default. |

**Irrigation VPD feedback:**
| Parameter | Range | Purpose |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| `irrig_vpd_boost_pct` | 0-100% | Extra irrigation duration when VPD stress sustained. |
| `irrig_vpd_boost_threshold_hrs` | 0.5-12 hrs | Hours of VPD stress before irrigation boost activates. |

**Switches:**
| Parameter | Values | Purpose |
|-----------|--------|---------|
| `sw_fog_closes_vent` | 0/1 | Close vent during fog to retain humidity (usually 1). |
| `sw_economiser_enabled` | 0/1 | Enthalpy-based vent gating (usually 1). |

